UDA presidential candidate William Ruto on Friday took his campaigns to Nandi, Busia and Bungoma counties. "The destiny of Kenya is in your hands. Make sure you are there to choose economic empowerment for all Kenyans through the Bottom-Up Economic Agenda on August 9. Thatâ€™s the PLAN," Ruto said. Ruto condemned those scheming to intimidate supporters and he reiterated a call for peace and calm at all times. "We owe this country a free, fair and democratic election devoid of manipulation by any state actors," he said. He was accompanied by ANC leader Musalia Mudavadi and Ford Kenya leader Moses Wetangula among others. His itinerary started at Kapsabet in Emgwen constituency before heading to Busia town. Ruto had on Thursday took his campaigns to Meru, Embu and Tharaka Nithi counties.